actor User
participant Client as React admin/API client
participant Auth as Auth routes
participant Security as Password/JWT/security services
participant AuthMW as auth_middleware
participant TenantMW as tenant_middleware
participant Limits as Rate-limit/quota services
participant Redis as Redis rate-limit counters
participant Org as Organization routes
participant Handler as Tenant route handler
participant RLS as RLS service
participant DB as PostgreSQL

rect rgb(238, 247, 255)
    Note over User,DB: Registration [IMPLEMENTED]
    User->>Client: Submit email, password, and name
    Client->>Auth: POST /api/auth/register
    Auth->>Auth: Validate fields and normalize email
    Auth->>Security: Argon2 password hash
    Auth->>DB: Count users to choose default global role
    critical Registration DB transaction [IMPLEMENTED]
        Auth->>DB: BEGIN
        Auth->>DB: INSERT users
        Auth->>DB: INSERT user_roles
        Auth->>DB: UPSERT active default organization membership
        Auth->>DB: Optionally assign default organization owner
        Auth->>DB: COMMIT
    option Any registration write fails
        DB-->>Auth: SQL error; transaction rolls back
        Auth-->>Client: Mapped error
    end
    Auth->>Security: Sign short-lived access JWT and generate refresh token
    Auth->>DB: INSERT hashed refresh token and expiry
    Note over Auth,DB: Refresh-token insertion occurs after the registration commit [PARTIAL]
    Auth-->>Client: Access token, user, memberships, default organization
    Auth-->>Client: Set-Cookie zinhar_refresh_token; HttpOnly; SameSite=Lax; Path=/api/auth
end

rect rgb(238, 255, 242)
    Note over User,DB: Login, failed-login tracking, and rate limiting [IMPLEMENTED]
    User->>Client: Submit credentials
    Client->>Auth: POST /api/auth/login with client address/forwarding headers
    Auth->>Security: Resolve client IP
    Auth->>DB: Count recent failed login_attempts for IP
    alt Failure threshold reached
        Security-->>Auth: TooManyRequests
        break Login is rate limited
            Auth-->>Client: 429 mapped error
        end
    else Login allowed
        Auth->>DB: Load active user and highest-priority global role
        alt User missing
            Auth->>DB: INSERT failed login_attempt
            Auth-->>Client: 401 generic invalid credentials
        else User found
            Auth->>Security: Verify Argon2 password
            alt Password invalid
                Auth->>DB: INSERT failed login_attempt
                Auth-->>Client: 401 generic invalid credentials
            else Password valid
                Auth->>DB: INSERT successful login_attempt
                Auth->>Security: Sign access JWT and generate refresh token
                Auth->>DB: INSERT hashed refresh token and expiry
                Auth-->>Client: Auth JSON plus refresh cookie
            end
        end
    end
end

rect rgb(250, 248, 255)
    Note over Client,DB: Refresh-token rotation [IMPLEMENTED, NON-ATOMIC]
    Client->>Auth: POST /api/auth/refresh with credentialed refresh cookie
    Auth->>Security: Hash presented refresh token
    Auth->>DB: Find unrevoked, unexpired token for active user
    alt Token missing, expired, revoked, or replayed
        Auth-->>Client: 401 invalid refresh token
    else Valid refresh record
        Auth->>DB: UPDATE old token revoked_at = now()
        Auth->>Security: Sign new access JWT and generate new refresh token
        Auth->>DB: INSERT new hashed refresh token
        alt New token insertion succeeds
            Auth-->>Client: New access token and replacement refresh cookie
        else New token insertion fails after revocation
            Note over Auth,DB: No transaction or replacement linkage restores the old token [DECISION REQUIRED]
            Auth-->>Client: Mapped database error
        end
    end
end

rect rgb(255, 248, 238)
    Note over Client,DB: Logout [IMPLEMENTED]
    Client->>AuthMW: POST /api/auth/logout with Bearer access token and optional refresh cookie/body
    AuthMW->>Security: Verify access JWT
    AuthMW->>Auth: Add Claims and continue
    opt Refresh token is supplied
        Auth->>Security: Hash refresh token
        Auth->>DB: Revoke matching unrevoked refresh_tokens row
    end
    Auth-->>Client: Clear refresh cookie with Max-Age=0
    Note over Client,Auth: Access JWT is not persisted or server-revoked; the client discards it [IMPLEMENTED LIMITATION]
end

rect rgb(255, 252, 238)
    Note over Client,DB: Authenticated tenant-aware request and RLS context [IMPLEMENTED]
    Client->>AuthMW: Request with Authorization: Bearer token and X-Organization-Id
    AuthMW->>Security: Verify access JWT
    alt JWT absent, invalid, or expired
        AuthMW-->>Client: 401
    else JWT valid
        AuthMW->>TenantMW: Claims extension
        TenantMW->>TenantMW: Parse X-Organization-Id
        TenantMW->>DB: Load active organization and active membership for claims.sub
        alt Membership or organization is not active
            TenantMW-->>Client: 403
        else Active membership
            TenantMW->>Limits: Check organization/user request rate
            Limits->>DB: Load organization_rate_limits settings
            Limits->>Redis: Increment/check organization and user counters
            alt Redis rate-limit operation fails
                Limits-->>TenantMW: Redis error
                TenantMW-->>Client: Mapped request error; no rate-limit fallback
            else Rate limit allows request
                opt Path is not /api/billing*
                    TenantMW->>Limits: Check plan API quota and increment usage_counters
                    Limits->>DB: Read plan/usage and UPSERT API request counter
                end
                TenantMW->>TenantMW: Attach Claims and TenantContext
                TenantMW->>Handler: Continue with Claims and TenantContext
                opt Handler uses a tenant RLS helper
                    Handler->>RLS: Request tenant connection/transaction
                    RLS->>DB: set_config organization_id, user_id, rls_bypass=false
                    RLS->>DB: Execute tenant query under PostgreSQL policies
                    DB-->>Handler: Tenant-scoped result
                end
                Handler-->>Client: JSON response or mapped error
            end
        end
    end
end

rect rgb(255, 238, 245)
    Note over Client,DB: Organization invitation acceptance [IMPLEMENTED]
    Client->>AuthMW: POST /api/organization-invitations/accept with Bearer token
    AuthMW->>Org: Claims extension and token JSON
    Org->>Security: Hash invitation token
    critical Membership and invitation transaction [IMPLEMENTED]
        Org->>DB: BEGIN
        Org->>DB: Load pending, unexpired invitation matching current user email
        Org->>Limits: Ensure organization member capacity
        Limits->>DB: Read current plan and active membership count
        Org->>DB: UPSERT organization_members as active with invited role
        Org->>DB: UPDATE invitation to accepted with accepted_at
        Org->>DB: COMMIT
    option Invalid/expired token, email mismatch, quota failure, or SQL error
        DB-->>Org: Error; transaction rolls back when dropped
        Org-->>Client: Mapped error
    end
    Org->>DB: Record organization.invitation.accept audit event after commit
    Note over Org,DB: Audit failure cannot roll back accepted membership [PARTIAL]
    Org->>DB: Reload organization membership
    Org-->>Client: Accepted membership JSON
end
